Hey everyone!

My name is Peter K and I am running for Dean of Students. Over the past few days I'm sure you've seen some of my posters around campus. To let you all know a little bit about me: I am very upbeat, although I have a more somber tone on a host of #OnlyatGW issues. I believe that all people have the right to more GWorld, dorms where the roof doesn't collapse, gallery mozzarella sticks, and more. I believe that a key item that is often under attack on campus is how Deli isn't open on Sunday. I'm sure many of you have experienced negativity, to say the least, about having to live on the Vern; I am running for Dean of Students to get the University to act in solidarity with students, and to make effective changes in the attitudes toward those of us that don't hold the same views as most of our administration. Come out to the GBM tomorrow at 8:30 and let your voice be heard. After all your vote is your voice, and our collective voices can be a powerful thing. The time is Now to join me in making College Effective again!
